_the_Summer_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Jul\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 3}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paris 2024 Olympic Summer Games\", \"from\": 99, \"to\": 134}, {\"ngram\": \"Chateau de Versailles\", \"from\": 138, \"to\": 159}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Mandatory Credit: Andrew Nelles-USA TODAY Sports Andrew Nelles-USA TODAY Sports PARIS - Horse welfare has been a major topic of conversation around the equestrian competition at the Olympics, and the scandal involving champion rider Charlotte Dujardin has attracted the attention of leaders in a related sport.\", \"from\": 161, \"to\": 473, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 315, \"end\": 325, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Equestrian_at_the_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9833712654222647, \"rank\": 0.016909925236286795, \"text\": \"equestrian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Equestrian_at_the_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Equestrian_at_the_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 396, \"end\": 414, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charlotte_Dujardin\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Charlotte Dujardin\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charlotte_Dujardin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charlotte_Dujardin\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Mandatory Credit\", \"from\": 161, \"to\": 177}, {\"ngram\": \"USA TODAY\", \"from\": 193, \"to\": 202}, {\"ngram\": \"USA TODAY\", \"from\": 224, \"to\": 233}, {\"ngram\": \"a major topic\", \"from\": 272, \"to\": 285}, {\"ngram\": \"conversation\", \"from\": 289, \"to\": 301}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 339, \"to\": 351}, {\"ngram\": \"the scandal\", \"from\": 357, \"to\": 368}, {\"ngram\": \"champion rider\", \"from\": 379, \"to\": 393}, {\"ngram\": \"the attention\", \"from\": 427, \"to\": 440}, {\"ngram\": \"leaders\", \"from\": 444, \"to\": 451}, {\"ngram\": \"a related sport\", \"from\": 455, \"to\": 470}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Prominent members of the horse racing community consider the situation another lesson for an industry that has made significant changes in recent years in the name of safety and still has work to do to regain the public's trust.\", \"from\": 475, \"to\": 703, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Prominent members\", \"from\": 475, \"to\": 492}, {\"ngram\": \"the horse racing community\", \"from\": 496, \"to\": 522}, {\"ngram\": \"the situation\", \"from\": 532, \"to\": 545}, {\"ngram\": \"an industry\", \"from\": 565, \"to\": 576}, {\"ngram\": \"significant changes\", \"from\": 591, \"to\": 610}, {\"ngram\": \"recent years\", \"from\": 614, \"to\": 626}, {\"ngram\": \"the name\", \"from\": 630, \"to\": 638}, {\"ngram\": \"safety\", \"from\": 642, \"to\": 648}, {\"ngram\": \"the public's trust\", \"from\": 684, \"to\": 702}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"If you are involved in a horse sport, be it polo, be it dressage, be it show jumping, be it horse racing, the priority has to be the welfare of the horse,\\\" said Lisa Lazarus, CEO of the Horseracing Integrity and Safety Authority that oversees the sport in the U.S. \\\"If that is not the priority and if it is not kind of clear to the public and to regulators that the horse is being prioritized and its welfare is being prioritized, the sport will be in jeopardy.\\\"\", \"from\": 705, \"to\": 1168, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 867, \"end\": 879, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lisa_Lazarus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Lisa Lazarus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lisa_Lazarus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lisa_Lazarus\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a horse sport\", \"from\": 729, \"to\": 742}, {\"ngram\": \"polo\", \"from\": 750, \"to\": 754}, {\"ngram\": \"the priority\", \"from\": 812, \"to\": 824}, {\"ngram\": \"the welfare\", \"from\": 835, \"to\": 846}, {\"ngram\": \"the horse\", \"from\": 850, \"to\": 859}, {\"ngram\": \"CEO\", \"from\": 881, \"to\": 884}, {\"ngram\": \"the Horseracing Integrity and Safety Authority\", \"from\": 888, \"to\": 934}, {\"ngram\": \"the sport\", \"from\": 949, \"to\": 958}, {\"ngram\": \"the U.S.\", \"from\": 962, \"to\": 970}, {\"ngram\": \"the priority\", \"from\": 987, \"to\": 999}, {\"ngram\": \"the public\", \"from\": 1034, \"to\": 1044}, {\"ngram\": \"regulators\", \"from\": 1052, \"to\": 1062}, {\"ngram\": \"the horse\", \"from\": 1068, \"to\": 1077}, {\"ngram\": \"its welfare\", \"from\": 1103, \"to\": 1114}, {\"ngram\": \"the sport\", \"from\": 1137, \"to\": 1146}, {\"ngram\": \"jeopardy\", \"from\": 1158, \"to\": 1166}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Video of Dujardin repeatedly striking a horse caused the three-time Olympic gold medalist to withdraw from the Paris Games and led to a provisional suspension from the International Federation for Equestrian Sports, or FEI.\", \"from\": 1170, \"to\": 1393, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1389, \"end\": 1392, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Federation_for_Equestrian_Sports\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4920359798164935e-48, \"text\": \"FEI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Federation_for_Equestrian_Sports\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Federation_for_Equestrian_Sports\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Video\", \"from\": 1170, \"to\": 1175}, {\"ngram\": \"Dujardin\", \"from\": 1179, \"to\": 1187}, {\"ngram\": \"a horse\", \"from\": 1208, \"to\": 1215}, {\"ngram\": \"the three-time Olympic gold medalist\", \"from\": 1223, \"to\": 1259}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paris Games\", \"from\": 1277, \"to\": 1292}, {\"ngram\": \"a provisional suspension\", \"from\": 1304, \"to\": 1328}, {\"ngram\": \"the International Federation\", \"from\": 1334, \"to\": 1362}, {\"ngram\": \"Equestrian Sports\", \"from\": 1367, \"to\": 1384}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And it did not stop there: Carlos Parro was issued a warning after an animal rights group sent the FEI's president photos and evidence of the Brazil rider hyper-flexing a horse's neck in a prohibited move known as \\\"Rollkur\\\" that can compromise breathing.\", \"from\": 1394, \"to\": 1648, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1493, \"end\": 1496, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Federation_for_Equestrian_Sports\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4920359798164935e-48, \"text\": \"FEI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Federation_for_Equestrian_Sports\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Federation_for_Equestrian_Sports\"}, {\"begin\": 1536, \"end\": 1542, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil\", \"score\": 0.9991436051199901, \"rank\": 0.0008562780971584564, \"text\": \"Brazil\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil\"}, {\"begin\": 1609, \"end\": 1616, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rollkur\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Rollkur\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rollkur\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rollkur\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Carlos Parro\", \"from\": 1421, \"to\": 1433}, {\"ngram\": \"a warning\", \"from\": 1445, \"to\": 1454}, {\"ngram\": \"an animal rights group\", \"from\": 1461, \"to\": 1483}, {\"ngram\": \"evidence\", \"from\": 1520, \"to\": 1528}, {\"ngram\": \"a horse's neck\", \"from\": 1563, \"to\": 1577}, {\"ngram\": \"a prohibited move\", \"from\": 1581, \"to\": 1598}, {\"ngram\": \"breathing\", \"from\": 1638, \"to\": 1647}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The public backlash comes three years after a Germany coach was suspended from the Tokyo Olympics for striking an uncooperative horse.\", \"from\": 1650, \"to\": 1784, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1696, \"end\": 1703, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany\", \"score\": 0.9893552155687897, \"rank\": 0.